Please tell us generally about how we can help. Note : Form submissions will be visible to the student and employees supporting student success. Personal information unrelated to the request or of a sensitive nature should not be included on the form . Typical response time: 3 - 7 business days To book an appointment with your Student Success Advisor (SSA) and view their drop-in schedule, visit the SSA Appointments page . For concerns about well-being, mental health or behavioural issues, please submit a Care Team referral . Absences Academic Integrity College not meeting my expectations Co-op, field placement, or hands on learning Deadlines / tests Failing, withdrawing or discontinued Further education after this Interactions with peers in my classes Learning strategies and skills Scheduling issues Understanding college in Canada Registration concerns Other Personal Concerns Your form submission will be reviewed by a member of the Student Success Advising team. When it comes to personal matters, we can assist you with finding the right support to meet your needs. In some cases, that might be general assistance by a member of our team, and in others we may help you connect with a specialist in another department who can go into more detail. If mental health is central to your current situation, please consider a Care Team referral linked above. Career plans and long-term goals Finances, tuition and student fees Housing or living arrangements Job issues or seeking employment Community or sense of belonging Disability or accessibility Health or well-being Interpersonal relationships (friends, roommates, family, etc.) Work permits or study visas Other Additional Information (required) Please provide clarification about your concerns to help us connect you with the appropriate support. Manually sent by Administrators × Close Sponsored Communications Sponsored communications are sent by Conestoga College on behalf of other parties (eg: employers, community organisations). Manually sent by Administrators × Close Personalised Communications Personalised communications are based on specific searches on your study area, skills, experiences or other criteria.

students under the legal authority of the Ontario Colleges of Applied Arts and Technology Act and ensures the personal information is managed in compliance with the Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act in order offer students a comprehensive program of career-oriented, post-secondary education and training. The purpose of the Student Success Portal is to provide students with one shared system that enables students to self-book appointments with a variety of service teams at the College. As such, service teams will create consultation notes for students to review. These may include appointment notes and recommended actions. Students can also access resources and request assistance via forms within the system where to ensure the relevant information can be used to support students in a timely and effective way. Students participating in Events & Activities are acknowledging the sharing of their information for the purposes of tracking booking, attendance and follow-up activities by college services and opportunity providers. Conestoga protects personal information and only discloses it as required by law. If you have any questions, please reach out to privacy@conestogac.on.ca . By accepting these terms, you consent to the Student Success Portal and the information sharing provisions within it.
